{
  "texts": [
    "It uses an automatic entropy adjustment to control the temperature parameter that determines the relative importance of the entropy term.",
    "The original algorithm is formulated for a continuous action space, but Christodoulou (2019) has extended it to discrete action spaces.",
    "The soft actor-critic algorithm for discrete action spaces is utilized in this work, with some adaptions discussed below.",
    "We adapt SAC to the setting where the state vectors are represented by the RNN outputs of the latest recurrent node.",
    "The actor is a neural network with parameters, providing probabilities (a|s) for an action a and state vec- tor s using a softmax layer."
  ]
}